**Section 1**
This section will resolve the following warnings:
1.5  - Ensure auditing is configured for the Docker daemon
1.6  - Ensure auditing is configured for Docker files and directories - /var/lib/docker
1.7  - Ensure auditing is configured for Docker files and directories - /etc/docker
1.10  - Ensure auditing is configured for Docker files and directories - /etc/default/docker

Remediation:
1)	Install auditctl.
sudo apt install auditd

2)	Go to this directory and edit the audit.rule file
cd  /etc/audit/rules.d
nano audit rules

3)	Add in the following rules and save the file.
-w /usr/bin/docker -p wa
-w /var/lib/docker -p wa
-w /etc/docker -p wa
-w /lib/systemd/system/docker.service -p wa
-w /lib/systemd/system/docker.socket -p wa
-w /etc/default/docker -p wa
-w /etc/docker/daemon.json -p wa
-w /usr/bin/docker-containerd -p wa
-w /usr/bin/docker-runc -p wa

4)	Restart the audit service
systemctl restart auditd


**Section 2**
This section will resolve the following warning:
2.14 - Ensure live restore is Enabled
Remediation:
1)	Create the /etc/docker/daemon.json if you do not have one. Edit the .json file to add in the following and save the file.
{
  "live-restore": true
}
2)	Restart the Docker daemon.
systemctl reload docker


